http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/BJP-submits-petition-against-MD-of-MPM/article14013335.ece

A delegation led by Bharatiya Janata Party leaders, including the former Chief Minister B.S. Yeddyurappa and Leader of the Opposition in the Legislative Council K.S. Eshwarappa, on Thursday submitted a petition against IAS officer Harsh Gupta, Managing Director, Mysore Paper Mills (MPM), Bhadravati — on laying off 1,100 employees of the factory — to Minister for Industries R.V. Deshpande.In the petition, they have demanded jobs for the MPM employees. Mr. Deshpande assured the delegation that he would look into the issue soon.The MPM’s management also plans to withdraw some perks being offered to the employees and enforce a ceiling on employers’ contribution to provident fund and reimbursement of medical expenses.In the petition, they have demanded jobs for the MPM employees who have been laid off